args:
When the party reaches the Dragon Necropolis,
they encounter the first Midgardsormr, who was
born from the Origin. They also learn how the
Primordial Windwyrm left part of his will behind
in case the Progenitor was ever revived.

If I have to see one more stupid grain of
sand I'm gonna LOSE IT, you guys!
How much further till we reach this
Dragon Necropolis place, anyway?
We are close—that much is certain.\nBut as for its exact location, I fear I am\nat a bit of a loss.
This was originally a massive lake.\nIt's said that at its bottom is a graveyard\nwhere the primordial dragons rest.
An old legend of Lefkos claimed it was\na place where dragons were reborn.
So Midgardsormr and Mym and all them\nwere reborn in THIS dump?
This place does not seem familiar to me\nin the slightest; before joining you, all I\ncan remember is being in my volcano.
All life is born of mana, and all will return\nto mana once more. That is especially true\nfor us dragons.
As you were born of flames, you must have\ntaken form in a place suitable for this.
Okay, so then what's all this chatter\nabout how you were ＂reborn＂ here?
It is but a legend, Notte. Perhaps it holds\nbut a mere kernel of the truth—or perhaps\nit is only the fantastic tale of a madman.
Yet I can say with all certainty that\nSOMETHING sleeps here.
Since our arrival here, I've felt as if\nsomeone is calling to me...
Must be one of those low-talker types,\nbecause I don't hear squat...
This is Midgardsormr we're talking about.\nThere may really be something here.
We'll simply need to keep moving and see.
So what happens when a dragon\nis reborn, anyway?
Dragons are more akin to a natural\nphenomenon than a typical being. It could\nbe said we are nature's will given form.
And among dragons there exist some that\nare even closer to pure mana. We Five\nGreatwyrms are one such instance.
Those who are close to mana in this way\nlive outside the bounds of the typical\nlife cycle.
One is born of parents. They grow. Age.\nProcreate. We are not part of that cycle.
Is that how it is for you too, Mym?
It is. I never had parents. In the moment\nI first achieved consciousness, I was\nalready a fully formed dragon.
However, in one way we are similar\nto all other life: we experience death.
When I eventually perish, my body and will\nshall be returned to mana, and a new\nMidgardsormr will be born somewhere.
And will this new Midgardsormr be\nentirely different from how you are now?
I believe our powers and appearance will\nbe much the same, as well as our general\nway of thinking.
But he will not have my memories.\nIndeed, I can barely remember anything\nfrom the time before I was reborn.
So the big lug Midgardsormr we all know\nand love is gonna be gone forever?\nDude, that sucks big time!
The old Midgardsormr really saved me\nback in the day, you know?
Apologies, but I hold no memory of that.
So you're not really the same\nMidgardsormr as the one from a\nthousand years ago...
But hey, what can you do, am I right?\nIt's just hard for me because of how\nsimilar the two of you are.
It must be hard to be forgotten by people\nyou've spent so much time with.
Oh, but worry not, darling!\nI'll NEVER forget you!
Still, I suppose you look a liiiittle different\nfrom the Windwyrm I knew.
Maybe it's because of this whole ＂losing\nyour powers when you're reborn＂ business.
That may be. We were not meant to have\nlost our powers when we were reborn,\nand yet we did.
If we can find our answers here—
I am Midgardsormr, and I have been\nwaiting for the one who bears that\nselfsame name of the wind.
Then you're the Midgardsormr from before\nour version was reborn?!
...You're very similar to the Midgardsormr\nI knew. It really brings back memories.
But I don't think you're him...
Nay, I am a far more ancient wind;\nI am the first and original Midgardsormr,\nhe who was born of the Origin.
That means you're one of the Five\nGreatwyrms who sealed away the\nProgenitor after his initial return.

In part—though in truth, I am naught but
the remnants of that dragon's memory and
will; a lingering breeze at the end of a
cool summer's day.
I have been waiting here for a new wind to\narrive should the day we feared approach\nonce more.
The day of the Progenitor's return.
I am but a portion of the original\nMidgardsormr's will, left here to pass on\nthe memory of ancient times.
So that's why it was said dragons rested\nin this place...
Sounds like we're both after the same\nthing then, which oughta hurry this whole\nthing up real nice.
You're likely already aware that Xenos—\nthe Progenitor—has been resurrected\nin this world.
We came here in search of a means\nto defeat him.
So tell us, Primordial Windwyrm.\nTell us how you faced the Progenitor.
